---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';

// Tool metadata
const name = "Headphone Test Suite";
const category = "audio";
const tier = "Audio Utilities";
const description = "Free online headphone test. Diagnostic utility to check left right headphone channels, frequency sweep limits, low-end bass, and driver dynamic response.";

const pageTitle = "Online Headphone Test - Left Right Audio & Sound Quality Check";
const canonicalUrl = "https://boardtools.app/tools/audio/headphone-test";
const ogImage = "/og/headphone-test.png";
const keywords = "headphone test, headphone test music, left right headphone test, headphone test left and right, left and right headphone test, online headphone test, right and left headphone test, headphone test left right, headphone test sound, audio headphone test, stereo headphone test";
---

<Layout 
  title={pageTitle}
  description={description}
  toolName={name}
  toolCategory={category}
  keywords={keywords}
  canonical={canonicalUrl}
  ogImage={ogImage}
  ogType="website"
  hideBanner={true}
>
  <!-- FAQ Page JSON-LD Schema -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How to test headphone?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>To perform an online headphone test, connect your headphones to your device, set your master volume to a safe level (around 50%), and run diagnostic tests. A comprehensive check includes testing the left and right audio channels for correct orientation, running a frequency sweep from 20 Hz to 20,000 Hz, testing sub-bass extension, and checking for driver rattle at high volumes.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How to test headphone microphone?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>You can test a headphone microphone by opening your operating system's sound settings or using an online mic testing tool. Select your headphone microphone as the input device, speak at a normal level, and observe the input volume meter. You can also record a short audio sample and play it back to check for clarity, static, or background hums.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How to test headphone sound quality before buying?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>To test headphone sound quality before buying, listen to a familiar playlist or high-quality headphone test music that spans various genres. Check the low-end sub-bass extension, the clarity of mid-range vocals, and the crispness of high-frequency treble. Additionally, check for a wide soundstage and natural imaging to ensure the instruments sound properly separated.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How to test headphone quality?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>Testing headphone quality involves checking frequency response limits, dynamic range, harmonic distortion, and build quality. High-quality headphones should reproduce sub-bass frequencies down to 20 Hz, scale volumes linearly without clipping or rattle, and keep crosstalk between channels to an absolute minimum.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How to test headphone mic on pc?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>On a PC, open Settings > System > Sound. Under the Input section, verify that your headphone mic is selected. Speak into the microphone and check the 'Test your microphone' volume bar. If the bar moves, your PC is receiving audio. Alternatively, you can use the Windows Voice Recorder app to record and listen to your voice.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How to test headphone frequency response?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>To test headphone frequency response, use a logarithmic frequency sweep tool. This sweeps from 20 Hz to 20,000 Hz in a smooth tone. Listen closely for any volume dips, sudden dropouts, or piercing resonances, which indicate an uneven frequency response curve.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How to test headphone soundstage?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>Test headphone soundstage by playing binaural audio recordings or tracks recorded with spatial audio. A wide soundstage creates the illusion that sounds are coming from around you in a three-dimensional space, rather than inside your head. Good soundstage headphones let you precisely pinpoint the direction and distance of instruments.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How to test left and right headphone?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>To perform a left and right headphone test, use a stereo channel balance test. This pulses audio exclusively to the left side, then to the right side, and finally to the center. Ensure the sound matches the physical tags on your headphones (L and R) and that both channels output equal volume.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How to test headphone noise cancelling?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>To test Active Noise Cancelling (ANC), play a simulated background noise, such as office chatter or plane cabin hum, through external speakers. Toggle the noise-cancelling mode on your headphones on and off to hear how much of the low-frequency rumble is blocked. Excellent ANC should significantly reduce constant low-frequency noise.</p>"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  </script>
  <section class="max-w-[1200px] w-full mx-auto px-4 py-3 sm:py-6 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:gap-4 animate-fade-in-up pb-16">
    <!-- Header Title Area -->
    <div class="border-b border-hairline pb-3 sm:pb-4 flex flex-col gap-2">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-1.5 text-stone text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider">
        <span>Audio Diagnostics</span>
        <span>•</span>
        <span class="text-brand-blue font-bold">Calibration Tools</span>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center justify-between mt-0.5 gap-2">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 flex-wrap">
          <h1 class="font-display font-medium text-lg sm:text-2xl tracking-tight text-primary">
            {name}
          </h1>
          <span
            class="bg-surface-pricing-featured text-brand-blue text-[9px] sm:text-[10px] py-0.5 px-2 rounded-full font-semibold uppercase whitespace-nowrap shrink-0"
            >{tier}</span
          >
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 flex-wrap">
          <button
            type="button"
            id="share-btn"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[11px] font-semibold px-2.5 py-1 bg-canvas hover:bg-surface border border-hairline text-slate hover:text-primary rounded-full transition-all cursor-pointer shadow-subtle"
            aria-label="Share tool link"
          >
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-3.5 h-3.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M8.684 10.742l5.028-2.513m0 7.544l-5.028-2.513M18 8a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm-6 8a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 0a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z" />
            </svg>
            <span>Share</span>
          </button>

          <button
            type="button"
            id="how-it-works-btn"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[11px] font-semibold px-2.5 py-1 bg-canvas hover:bg-surface border border-hairline text-slate hover:text-primary rounded-full transition-all cursor-pointer shadow-subtle"
            aria-label="How headphone test works"
          >
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-3.5 h-3.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
            </svg>
            <span>How it works</span>
          </button>

          <button
            type="button"
            id="reset-btn"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[11px] font-semibold px-2.5 py-1 bg-canvas hover:bg-surface border border-hairline text-slate hover:text-brand-coral hover:border-brand-coral rounded-full transition-all cursor-pointer shadow-subtle"
            aria-label="Reset inputs and output"
          >
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-3 h-3" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M4 4v5h.582m15.356 2A8.001 8.001 0 1121.21 7.89M9 11l3-3 3 3m-3-3v12"></path>
            </svg>
            <span>Reset</span>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Main Workspace Area -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-4 sm:gap-6 items-stretch">
      <!-- Left: Interactive workspace containing current test module / controls -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-8 flex flex-col gap-4 sm:gap-6">
        
        <!-- Activation Banner & Safety Controls -->
        <div class="card-base p-4 sm:p-5 flex flex-col gap-4 relative overflow-hidden">
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center justify-between gap-4">
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-1">
              <span class="text-[10px] font-bold text-slate uppercase tracking-wider">Device Configuration</span>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <input
                  type="text"
                  id="device-name"
                  placeholder="e.g. Sony WH-1000XM5"
                  class="text-input h-9 px-3 py-1.5 text-xs w-full sm:w-64 border border-hairline bg-surface rounded-md focus:border-brand-blue outline-none transition-colors"
                />
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Master Volume Control -->
            <div class="flex-1 max-w-xs flex flex-col gap-1">
              <div class="flex justify-between items-center text-[10px] font-bold text-slate uppercase">
                <span>Master Volume</span>
                <span id="volume-readout">50%</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-4 h-4 text-slate" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M15.536 8.464a5 5 0 010 7.072m2.828-9.9a9 9 0 010 12.728M5.586 15H4a1 1 0 01-1-1v-4a1 1 0 011-1h1.586l4.707-4.707C10.923 3.663 12 4.109 12 5v14c0 .891-1.077 1.337-1.707.707L5.586 15z" />
                </svg>
                <input
                  type="range"
                  id="master-volume"
                  min="0"
                  max="100"
                  value="50"
                  class="w-full h-1.5 bg-hairline rounded-lg appearance-none cursor-pointer accent-brand-blue"
                />
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Audio Initialization Gate -->
          <div id="audio-gate" class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-brand-yellow-deep/30 bg-yellow-light/20 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-3 text-xs text-yellow-dark">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="relative flex h-2 w-2">
                <span class="animate-ping absolute inline-flex h-full w-full rounded-full bg-brand-yellow-deep opacity-75"></span>
                <span class="relative inline-flex rounded-full h-2 w-2 bg-brand-yellow-deep"></span>
              </span>
              <span>Audio context is inactive. Tap to initialize and grant audio permissions.</span>
            </div>
            <button
              type="button"
              id="init-audio-btn"
              class="button-primary text-[11px] py-1 px-4 !rounded-full shadow-subtle transition-all cursor-pointer font-bold whitespace-nowrap bg-brand-yellow hover:bg-brand-yellow-deep text-primary border-none"
            >
              Start Audio Engine
            </button>
          </div>

          <!-- Safety Volume Warning -->
          <div id="volume-warning" class="hidden p-3 rounded-lg border border-brand-coral bg-coral-light/20 text-xs text-coral-dark flex items-center gap-2">
            <span>⚠️</span>
            <span class="font-medium">Caution: High volume settings can cause permanent hearing damage. Adjust gradually.</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Mode Toggle Slider -->
        <div class="flex rounded-full bg-surface p-0.5 border border-hairline w-full">
          <button
            type="button"
            id="mode-guided-btn"
            class="flex-1 text-center text-xs py-2 rounded-full font-bold transition-all cursor-pointer bg-primary text-canvas"
          >
            Guided Test Suite
          </button>
          <button
            type="button"
            id="mode-individual-btn"
            class="flex-1 text-center text-xs py-2 rounded-full font-bold transition-all cursor-pointer text-slate hover:text-primary"
          >
            Individual Diagnostic Tools
          </button>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 1: Guided Test Suite Sandbox -->
        <div id="guided-suite-panel" class="card-base p-6 flex flex-col gap-6">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between border-b border-hairline-soft pb-4">
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-1">
              <span class="text-[10px] font-bold text-brand-blue uppercase tracking-wider" id="guided-step-badge">Test 1 of 5</span>
              <h2 id="guided-step-title" class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary">Stereo Balance & Channel Test</h2>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Checklist UI of completed tests -->
            <div class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
              <div class="step-dot" data-step="1"></div>
              <div class="step-dot" data-step="2"></div>
              <div class="step-dot" data-step="3"></div>
              <div class="step-dot" data-step="4"></div>
              <div class="step-dot" data-step="5"></div>
              <div class="step-dot" data-step="6"></div>
              <div class="step-dot" data-step="7"></div>
              <div class="step-dot" data-step="8"></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Step Panels Container -->
          <div class="relative min-h-[320px] flex flex-col justify-center">
            
            <!-- Step 1: Stereo Balance -->
            <div id="guided-step-1" class="guided-step-content flex flex-col gap-4 sm:gap-6">
              <p class="text-xs text-slate max-w-md mx-auto text-center leading-relaxed">
                Confirm your left and right audio channels are connected correctly and outputting identical sound pressure. Click play to start cycling sounds.
              </p>
              
              <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 sm:gap-4 max-w-sm mx-auto w-full">
                <!-- Left Channel Box -->
                <div id="left-channel-indicator" class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center p-4 sm:p-6 border border-hairline rounded-xl bg-surface transition-all gap-2 sm:gap-3 text-center duration-300">
                  <span class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-slate">L</span>
                  <span class="text-[9px] sm:text-[10px] uppercase font-bold text-stone">Left Channel</span>
                  <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 sm:w-3 sm:h-3 rounded-full bg-brand-blue opacity-0 indicator-light"></div>
                </div>
                
                <!-- Right Channel Box -->
                <div id="right-channel-indicator" class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center p-4 sm:p-6 border border-hairline rounded-xl bg-surface transition-all gap-2 sm:gap-3 text-center duration-300">
                  <span class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-slate">R</span>
                  <span class="text-[9px] sm:text-[10px] uppercase font-bold text-stone">Right Channel</span>
                  <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 sm:w-3 sm:h-3 rounded-full bg-brand-teal opacity-0 indicator-light"></div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="flex justify-center gap-3">
                <button type="button" class="button-primary px-5 py-1.5 sm:px-6 sm:py-2 flex items-center gap-2 test-play-btn" data-test="stereo">
                  <span class="play-icon">▶ Play Test</span>
                  <span class="stop-icon hidden">■ Stop Test</span>
                </button>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Step 2: Frequency Sweep -->
            <div id="guided-step-2" class="guided-step-content hidden flex flex-col gap-4 sm:gap-6">
              <p class="text-xs text-slate max-w-md mx-auto text-center leading-relaxed">
                Sweeps from 30Hz up to 18,000Hz (18kHz) in a smooth logarithmic ramp. Listen for dead spots, volume dips, or harsh resonances.
              </p>

              <!-- Sweep Progress Visualizer -->
              <div class="w-full max-w-md mx-auto bg-surface border border-hairline rounded-xl p-4 sm:p-6 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:gap-4">
                <div class="flex justify-between items-baseline">
                  <span class="text-[10px] font-bold text-slate uppercase">Current Pitch</span>
                  <span id="sweep-frequency-readout" class="font-mono text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-brand-blue">30 Hz</span>
                </div>
                
                <div class="w-full bg-hairline h-1.5 sm:h-2 rounded-full overflow-hidden">
                  <div id="sweep-progress-bar" class="bg-brand-blue h-full w-0 transition-all duration-100 ease-linear"></div>
                </div>

                <div class="flex justify-between text-[9px] font-bold text-stone uppercase">
                  <span>30 Hz (Sub-Bass)</span>
                  <span>18 kHz (Treble)</span>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="flex justify-center gap-3">
                <button type="button" class="button-primary px-5 py-1.5 sm:px-6 sm:py-2 flex items-center gap-2 test-play-btn" data-test="sweep">
                  <span class="play-icon">▶ Play Sweep</span>
                  <span class="stop-icon hidden">■ Stop Sweep</span>
                </button>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Step 3: Bass Response -->
            <div id="guided-step-3" class="guided-step-content hidden flex flex-col gap-4 sm:gap-6">
              <p class="text-xs text-slate max-w-md mx-auto text-center leading-relaxed">
                Test low-frequency extension and consistency using precise sub-bass pulses. Select a frequency or cycle through each to inspect clarity.
              </p>

              <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-2 sm:gap-3">
                <button type="button" class="bass-btn px-3 py-1.5 sm:px-4 sm:py-2 border border-hairline rounded-lg text-xs bg-surface font-semibold text-primary transition-all hover:bg-canvas" data-freq="40">40 Hz (Deep Sub)</button>
                <button type="button" class="bass-btn px-3 py-1.5 sm:px-4 sm:py-2 border border-hairline rounded-lg text-xs bg-surface font-semibold text-primary transition-all hover:bg-canvas" data-freq="60">60 Hz (Sub-bass)</button>
                <button type="button" class="bass-btn px-3 py-1.5 sm:px-4 sm:py-2 border border-hairline rounded-lg text-xs bg-surface font-semibold text-primary transition-all hover:bg-canvas" data-freq="80">80 Hz (Mid-bass)</button>
                <button type="button" class="bass-btn px-3 py-1.5 sm:px-4 sm:py-2 border border-hairline rounded-lg text-xs bg-surface font-semibold text-primary transition-all hover:bg-canvas" data-freq="100">100 Hz (Upper-bass)</button>
              </div>

              <div class="flex justify-center gap-3">
                <button type="button" class="button-primary px-5 py-1.5 sm:px-6 sm:py-2 flex items-center gap-2 test-play-btn" data-test="bass">
                  <span class="play-icon">▶ Start Pulses</span>
                  <span class="stop-icon hidden">■ Stop Pulses</span>
                </button>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Step 4: Dynamic Range -->
            <div id="guided-step-4" class="guided-step-content hidden flex flex-col gap-4 sm:gap-6">
              <p class="text-xs text-slate max-w-md mx-auto text-center leading-relaxed">
                A sequence of tones decreasing in volume steps. Checks driver sensitivity, matching steps, and ambient isolation.
              </p>

              <!-- Dynamic range steps indicator -->
              <div class="flex justify-center items-end gap-2 max-w-sm mx-auto h-20 pb-2">
                <div class="dynamic-step w-10 flex flex-col items-center gap-1 transition-all duration-300" data-db="0">
                  <div class="w-full bg-slate-200 h-14 rounded-md relative overflow-hidden"><div class="absolute inset-x-0 bottom-0 bg-brand-blue transition-all duration-300 h-0 bar"></div></div>
                  <span class="text-[9px] font-bold text-stone">0dB</span>
                </div>
                <div class="dynamic-step w-10 flex flex-col items-center gap-1 transition-all duration-300" data-db="-10">
                  <div class="w-full bg-slate-200 h-10 rounded-md relative overflow-hidden"><div class="absolute inset-x-0 bottom-0 bg-brand-blue transition-all duration-300 h-0 bar"></div></div>
                  <span class="text-[9px] font-bold text-stone">-10dB</span>
                </div>
                <div class="dynamic-step w-10 flex flex-col items-center gap-1 transition-all duration-300" data-db="-20">
                  <div class="w-full bg-slate-200 h-7 rounded-md relative overflow-hidden"><div class="absolute inset-x-0 bottom-0 bg-brand-blue transition-all duration-300 h-0 bar"></div></div>
                  <span class="text-[9px] font-bold text-stone">-20dB</span>
                </div>
                <div class="dynamic-step w-10 flex flex-col items-center gap-1 transition-all duration-300" data-db="-30">
                  <div class="w-full bg-slate-200 h-5 rounded-md relative overflow-hidden"><div class="absolute inset-x-0 bottom-0 bg-brand-blue transition-all duration-300 h-0 bar"></div></div>
                  <span class="text-[9px] font-bold text-stone">-30dB</span>
                </div>
                <div class="dynamic-step w-10 flex flex-col items-center gap-1 transition-all duration-300" data-db="-40">
                  <div class="w-full bg-slate-200 h-3 rounded-md relative overflow-hidden"><div class="absolute inset-x-0 bottom-0 bg-brand-blue transition-all duration-300 h-0 bar"></div></div>
                  <span class="text-[9px] font-bold text-stone">-40dB</span>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="flex justify-center gap-3">
                <button type="button" class="button-primary px-5 py-1.5 sm:px-6 sm:py-2 flex items-center gap-2 test-play-btn" data-test="dynamic">
                  <span class="play-icon">▶ Play Steps</span>
                  <span class="stop-icon hidden">■ Stop Steps</span>
                </button>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Step 5: Driver Rattle/Distortion -->
            <div id="guided-step-5" class="guided-step-content hidden flex flex-col gap-4 sm:gap-6">
              <p class="text-xs text-slate max-w-md mx-auto text-center leading-relaxed">
                Plays a sustained sub-bass tone at a fixed 55Hz with a slowly rising volume. Listen closely for clicking, rattling, buzzing, or uneven vibration.
              </p>

              <!-- Safety Warning Banner -->
              <div class="p-3 bg-coral-light/20 border border-brand-coral text-coral-dark rounded-xl max-w-md mx-auto flex items-start gap-2.5 text-left transition-all duration-300" id="distortion-warn-card">
                <span class="text-sm mt-0.5">⚠️</span>
                <div class="flex flex-col gap-0.5">
                  <h4 class="font-bold text-[11px] uppercase tracking-wider">Safety Warning</h4>
                  <p class="text-[10px] leading-normal text-slate">
                    Stop the test immediately if you hear any rattle, severe buzz, or if the sound becomes uncomfortably loud. Do not force drivers past physical limits.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Ramp visualizer -->
              <div class="w-full max-w-sm mx-auto bg-surface border border-hairline rounded-lg h-5 relative overflow-hidden flex items-center justify-center">
                <div id="rattle-ramp-bar" class="absolute left-0 top-0 bottom-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-brand-blue via-brand-yellow to-brand-coral w-0 transition-all duration-100 ease-linear opacity-40"></div>
                <span id="rattle-ramp-readout" class="relative z-10 text-[10px] font-bold text-primary font-mono">0% Amplitude</span>
              </div>

              <div class="flex justify-center gap-3">
                <button type="button" class="button-primary px-5 py-1.5 sm:px-6 sm:py-2 flex items-center gap-2 test-play-btn" data-test="rattle">
                  <span class="play-icon">▶ Start Sweep</span>
                  <span class="stop-icon hidden">■ Stop Sweep</span>
                </button>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Step 6: Stereo Crosstalk Test -->
            <div id="guided-step-6" class="guided-step-content hidden flex flex-col gap-4 sm:gap-6">
              <p class="text-xs text-slate max-w-md mx-auto text-center leading-relaxed">
                Check stereo isolation. Pulses play in one channel while the other channel should remain completely silent. If you hear bleeding, your headphones or cable have crosstalk.
              </p>

              <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 sm:gap-4 max-w-sm mx-auto w-full">
                <!-- Left active box -->
                <div id="crosstalk-left-indicator" class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center p-4 border border-hairline rounded-xl bg-surface transition-all gap-1 text-center duration-300">
                  <span class="text-xl font-bold text-slate">Left Active</span>
                  <span class="text-[9px] uppercase font-bold text-stone">Listen to Left</span>
                  <div class="text-xs" id="crosstalk-left-label">Idle</div>
                </div>

                <!-- Right active box -->
